# Known memory-hog compiles: cap their parallelism (see env/low-mem) so a
# single heavy package can't OOM-kill the build on a memory-constrained
# runner. media-gfx/blender is the confirmed offender (run 26892007888 died
# at package 905/927); the rest are classic high-RAM-per-job builds and are
# no-ops when not present in @world.
media-gfx/blender        low-mem
dev-qt/qtwebengine       low-mem
media-libs/webkit-gtk    low-mem
app-office/libreoffice   low-mem
www-client/chromium      low-mem
www-client/firefox       low-mem
